parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy with excessive force, causing harm to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in an accident
airbag warning light is on
horn not working
loud vibration when gas pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has caused inconvenience and stress for vehicle owners, as they are unable to get their vehicles repaired due to a lack of available parts, leaving them with a potentially unsafe vehicle.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available for repair
dealership unable to provide a specific date for repair
loaner vehicle provided but of smaller quality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spiral cable assembly can cause the horn to stop functioning, which can lead to a safety issue, as the horn is an important warning device for other drivers.
symptoms: Horn stopped functioning
spiral cable assembly diagnosed as the cause of horn failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clock Spring Failure in Steering Wheel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring in the steering wheel can cause the horn to malfunction, which can lead to a lack of warning to other drivers in emergency situations, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The horn only works when the steering wheel is not in the forward position
the horn does not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver's Side Tail Light Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated shorting out of the driver's side tail light assembly can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The driver's side tail light repeatedly shorts out while driving
the tail light assembly has been replaced multiple times
bulbs have been replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent damage to the electrical wiring can cause various electrical system failures, leading to unexpected shutdowns, loss of critical systems, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Wires are damaged or eaten away by rodents
multiple electrical components have failed
including fuel injectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause unexpected loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly cuts off
all lights on the instrument panel come on
the engine turns over but won't start
the problem is intermittent and may not be reproducible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the heated seat can cause a burning smell, overheating, and potentially a fire, which can lead to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: A burning smell comes from the driver's seat
the heating switch will not turn off
the driver's side seat is extremely hot.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Body and Frame Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of body and frame components can lead to structural weakening, potentially causing accidents or injuries due to loss of vehicle integrity.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the gas tank strap
main guard
hatch release
liftgate
doors
and skid plate; holes or separations in the steel frame; detachment of components such as the power liftgate arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power liftgate can cause the door to fall unexpectedly, potentially causing injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Power liftgate arm detaches from the liftgate; stripped or loose screws; liftgate fails to stay in open position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the liftgate struts can cause the door to fall unexpectedly, potentially causing injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Liftgate fails to stay in open position; sudden failure of liftgate struts.
